Document_summary: This document is an application by Hawaiian Electric Company seeking approval for a Power Purchase Agreement with Waiawa PV, LLC for a 45.9 MW AC net photovoltaic project in Waiawa, O'ahu. The document outlines the project's alignment with the Commission's Inclinations and the State's energy policy goals, emphasizing the importance of the Project in integrating low-cost renewable generation in Hawai'i. It also discusses the financial implications and regulatory considerations related to the project.

This document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement between Hawaiian Electric Company, Inc. and Kalaeloa Solar Two, LLC. It outlines the terms and conditions of the agreement, including the construction and operation of a 5 MW photovoltaic energy facility. The document also discusses the implications of the agreement on Hawaiian Electric's system and the renewable energy goals of Hawaii.
